Hey dude.

I've tried and debugged. Obviously dubbo doesn't support properties placeholder or spel.

For example, when I set the annotation parameters as below.

      @service(interfaceClass = xxx.class, timeout = 3000, version = "1.0.7", group="#{config.group}")

It would throw exception as below when DubboProviderAutoConfiguration was running.

      Invalid group="${config.group}" contain illegal charactor, only digit, letter, '-', '_' and '.' is legal.

The exception is thrown from the 'setGroup' method of AbstractServiceConfig. Codes as below:

        public void setGroup(String group) {
        checkKey("group", group);
        this.group = group;
        }

        protected static void checkKey(String property, String value) {
        checkProperty(property, value, MAX_LENGTH, PATTERN_KEY);
        }

    protected static void checkProperty(String property, String value, int maxlength, Pattern pattern) {
        if (value == null || value.length() == 0) {
            return;
        }
        if (value.length() > maxlength) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("Invalid " + property + "=\"" + value + "\" is longer than " + maxlength);
        }
        if (pattern != null) {
            Matcher matcher = pattern.matcher(value);
            if (!matcher.matches()) {
                throw new IllegalStateException("Invalid " + property + "=\"" + value + "\" contain illegal charactor, only digit, letter, '-', '_' and '.' is legal.");
            }
        }
    }

> @yintiefu 如你所描述的，2.7.2版本确实和2.7.1存在以上差异。
> 
> 2.7.2开始会在每次调用后清空RpcContext，对于不清空context的场景我们也收到了一些用户上报的问题，如造成不同thread/调用间互相影响等，最终经过论我们决定采用清空context的策略。
> 抱歉给你带来以上不兼容性问题，你可以尝试用以下代码：
> 
> ```java
> CompletableFuture<Object> future = ref.$invokeAsync(callMethod, typeArrays, objectArrays);
> future.whenComplete(() -> {
>    String uri = RpcContext.getContext().getUrl().toFullString();
>    event.setTotalUri(uri);
> });
> 
> // 或者
> ref.$invokeAsync(callMethod, typeArrays, objectArrays);
> CompletableFuture<Object> future = RpcContext.getContext().getFuture();
> future.whenComplete(() -> {
>    String uri = RpcContext.getContext().getUrl().toFullString();
>    event.setTotalUri(uri);
> });
> ```

尝试这个方式无效，会先执行RpcContext.removeContext(),然后才是future.whenComplete

好像要使用whenCompleteWithContext，  异步调用的RpcContext会在AsyncRpcResult保留下来，调用whenCompleteWithContext时会把保留的RpcContext会恢复到当前线程上


AsyncRpcResult asyncRpcResult = ref.$invokeAsync(callMethod, typeArrays, objectArrays);
asyncRpcResult.whenCompleteWithContext((result,t) -> {
   String uri = RpcContext.getContext().getUrl().toFullString();
   event.setTotalUri(uri);
});

上面是2.7.3的

2.7.2要这样
asyncRpcResult.thenApplyWithContext((r)->{
    String uri = RpcContext.getContext().getUrl().toFullString();
    event.setTotalUri(uri);
    return r;
});

// 或者
AsyncRpcResult asyncRpcResult = ref.$invokeAsync(callMethod, typeArrays, objectArrays);
String uri = asyncRpcResult.getStoredContext().getUrl().toFullString();
event.setTotalUri(uri);

需要在
```java
   registries.stream().filter(RegistryConfig::isZookeeperProtocol).findFirst().ifPresent(rc -> {
            // we use the loading status of DynamicConfiguration to decide whether ConfigCenter has been initiated.
            Environment.getInstance().getDynamicConfiguration().orElseGet(() -> {
                ConfigManager configManager = ConfigManager.getInstance();
                ConfigCenterConfig cc = configManager.getConfigCenter().orElse(new ConfigCenterConfig());
                cc.setProtocol(rc.getProtocol());
                cc.setAddress(rc.getAddress());
                cc.setHighestPriority(false);
                cc.setClient(rc.getClient)); // 改进
                setConfigCenter(cc);
                startConfigCenter();
                return null;
            });
        });
```
`ConfigCenterConfig`中应该增加client属性，以将zk的`ZookeeperTransporter`方式传递给`ConfigCenterConfig`，保证此处zk客户端初始化和`ZookeeperRegistry`初始化zk客户端的方式一样。

目前看，通过显式配置 application logger 会有这样的警告信息，
比如: `applicationConfig.setLogger("slf4j")`

